{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0e8a7cf-eb73-4cd6-9a5c-dbc3a81c97a0","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{\n  \"sdk\": {\n    \"version\": \"11.0.100\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Additional steps:**\n- Update NuGet package references (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and migration guide for any API changes.\n- If you use a CI pipeline, update any SDK installer tasks to `11.0.x`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0ddd9bb-a5f3-4fdc-9b93-80cdcf9f0582","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no tools needed.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three files they mentioned.","outputTokens":330,"requestId":"0407:349DAE:713123:81B8B6:6A052A30"},"id":"e8a73d35-b621-46b2-b569-df470635fc80","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:49:44.221Z","parentId":"5e102723-dfe9-45fe-8d43-b036514caf73"}
